I mean being organized and keeping things under control is what helps me remain calm for the next day so yeah, I always like planning out what I'm gonna do each day, down to the smallest thing cause it makes me feel organized and in control of my time.. So yeah, I do use a to-do list each and everyday to plan out my day.."」

responses.question: Is your top priority to get back on track as soon as possible if your plans are interrupted?
responses.response_open: Harry: 「".....Yeah-? In general, whenever my plans are interrupted, I just want things to be back on track as soon as possible... I don't really like when something is suddenly interrupted my plan, I just like everything to run smoothly without interruptions.. I kind of don't like it when things doesn't go according to plan so yeah, I'm quite a plan type of person and I don't like my plans to be disrupted and interrupted cause it would mean I would have to rearrange things all over again and that stress me out..."」

responses.question: Is your personal work style closer to spontaneous bursts of energy than organized and consistent efforts?
responses.response_open: Harry: 「"...yeah, I'm more of a spontaneous person than an organized one, especially when it comes to work. I usually have sudden burst of energy where I'll just suddenly have the motivation and will power to do work and that is my time to work quickly and try to get things don as quickly as possible. After that I'll be just tired and burnt out and I'll take a break and after a moment and I'll probably have another burst of energy or maybe I would just keep feeling burnt out-..So yeah, my entire work style is pretty much spontaneous..」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant's responses indicate a preference for structure, planning, and a desire to have things under control. They express a strong inclination towards sticking with decisions once made, using a to-do list for daily planning, and a discomfort with interruptions to their plans. However, there is also an element of spontaneity in their work style, indicating some flexibility and openness.

responses.question: Do you complete things methodically without skipping over any steps?
responses.response_open: Harry: 「"Yes, actually. I always prefer to carefully and meticulously complete every task without skipping a step. I feel more comfortable when I complete things in a orderly and careful way without missing or skipping over anything. I like to have everything just done properly and perfectly.. and I don't really like the idea of skipping over anything when finishing a task, it's just something I just don't get why you can't finish a task properly?"」

responses.question: Do you struggle with deadlines?
responses.response_open: Harry: 「"Yeah... I kinda do, honestly. I'm just not good with deadlines, I find it hard for myself to finish things on time and the stress of the whole deadline just makes me procrastinate more.. Sometimes I just felt like I just need more time and having a deadline just puts me under so much pressure and stress.. So yeah, I do struggle with a deadline but I guess if I have to rush things, I do know how to make a quick decision but more often than not I would take too long trying to make a decision and ended up not doing anything.."」

responses.question: Do you feel confident that things will work out for you?
responses.response_open: Harry: 「"...not really, to be honest but I do try my best to stay positive. I mean- there's just always this slight feeling of doubt and uncertainty for things to work out for me at the back of my mind but I just try to push it aside and stay confident and positive. But deep down? No, I'm not that confident that things will actually work out for me..."」

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant seems to exhibit a preference for both Judging (J) and Perceiving (P) traits. They express a strong inclination towards completing tasks in an orderly and meticulous manner, which aligns with Judging characteristics. However, they also struggle with deadlines and exhibit a tendency to postpone decisions, indicating Perceiving traits.
